Overview
Extract structured voting data from scanned Thai election result documents (Form สส.6/1) from the 2026 Thai general election.

Given PNG scans of official election documents, your task is to:

Locate the correct row for each party in the voting tables
Extract the corresponding vote count
Convert all numbers to Arabic digits (0-9)
Party names are pre-filled in the submission template — you only need to predict the vote counts.

This is a test-set-only competition. There is no training data. You are expected to use existing OCR tools, Vision LLMs, or APIs. The focus is on prompt engineering, post-processing, and pipeline design.
